settings.title: What is Shopify?
settings.answer: Shopify is the world’s most powerful e-commerce platform that allows anyone to easily sell online, at a retail location, and everywhere in between.

settings.title: How do I setup my store?
settings.answer:
When you buy this theme you get full access to our comprehensive and easy to follow instructions on setting up the theme for your store.
If you’re looking for more generic Shopify store setup instructions, there are plenty of resources available on Shopify’s own website.

settings.title: Do I need a Designer/Programmer for my store?
settings.answer: We’ve designed the theme to be as flexible and configurable as possible but also made it simple to use. You would only need a designer/developer if you wanted to custom code something that the theme doesn’t do natively.

settings.title: Where can I buy this theme?
settings.answer: We only sell this theme at Themeforest, you can buy there. If you need a trial version, please contact apollotheme@gmail.com

settings.title: When you purchase a theme is that a one-time fee?
settings.answer: Yes, unlike other themes, you get free upgrades and support for 6-months and you only pay a one-time fee, unless stated otherwise.

settings.title: Can I trial a theme before buying it?
settings.answer: Yes, please contact us via email apollotheme@gmail.com

settings.title: Can I use the theme for multiple shops?
settings.answer: All of our themes are subject to a one-store license, so if you want to utilize the same theme in several live stores, you’ll have to purchase multiple licenses.

settings.title: Does this theme work with all Shopify plans?
settings.answer: Yes, it works with all plans.

settings.title: Is it necessary to pay for the service to setup the store?
settings.answer: No, we’ve designed the theme to be as intuitive to use as possible and we have also provided step-by-step instructions inside our theme description.

settings.title: What is the scope of your support?
settings.answer: Our support includes general inquiries regarding theme functionality; help with customizing the theme settings and any observed defect or theme issues. It doesn’t cover issues, such as errors due to third- party plugins or as an after effect of changes made to the theme code. For the full details on the extent of our support, please visit our Support Policy page.

settings.title: What if I need help with Shopify issues?
settings.answer: General shop inquiries, such as uploading products, creating collections, adding discount codes, managing domains, etc. can be best addressed by reaching Shopify Support specifically and/or by checking on their broad documentation accessible in the Shopify Manual.

settings.title: How fast do you respond to support inquiries?
settings.answer: We aim to give feedback to all requests within 24 hours, but please allow 1-2 business days for the response. Our support team is primarily based in the UTC +7 and is available during standard business hours. We have a weekend staff to answer basic queries too.

settings.title: Do you provide phone support? What about Skype?
settings.answer:
We don’t offer telephone or video call support as of now.

Support skype: nvchien91

settings.title: How does your diaper fit compare to other brands?
settings.answer:
Our diapers are generally sized bigger and in between sizes of the usual conventional brands. 

We recommend you to refer our sizing chart and choose the size based on your baby’s current weight. 

If you have any questions about sizing, you may contact our friendly customer service at support@offspringus.com and we are happy to assist you.

settings.title: Can wrong size cause any issue?
settings.answer:
Wrong sizing, such as too loose or too tight in any area will cause issues like leakages, blowouts and rashes. 

For instance, if you chosen a size bigger than your baby should be wearing, there is high chance of leakages or blowouts. 

Over sizing issue indications:
- Leaking from the side or any parts of the diaper and the diaper is not fully absorbed and light.
- Diaper is pulled above the belly button and high waist. 

Under sizing issue indications:
- Overflow urine from a fully absorbed diaper. 
- High content of moisture cause rashes as the capacity of absorbency has max out causing wetness on the topsheet.
- Skin irritation , redness around the thighs and waist.
- Diaper sits below the belly button

A good diaper fit indications:
- Snug fit, sit comfortably on the baby's waists and thighs
- front part of the diaper sits on top of your baby's belly's button.

settings.title: How does the elastic waistband plays an important role for a diaper?
settings.answer:
The waistband plays an important role to keep your baby snug fit and comfortable at the same time. A super stretchy waistband can help with the following:

- Prevent blowout from the back of your baby’s bottom.
- To keep poo in place and not leaking out from the back of your baby's waist.
- Snug fit, but flexible enough to cater for your baby's expanding belly, especially after feeding

settings.title: When should my baby move to a larger size?
settings.answer:
You should upsize your baby diapers when you notice the following:

- The diaper is filling up very soon as compare to previous and started to leak.
- The elastic band has expanded to the max and tight on your baby’s waist
- When the diaper is sitting below your baby’s belly button

settings.title: When is the right time for my baby to switch to diaper pants?
settings.answer: Our diaper pants are suitable for babies who start to crawl and stand, as young as 6 - 8 months old, you can start with size M for our diaper pants.

settings.title: Do your diapers come with wetness indicator?
settings.answer: Our diapers do not come with wetness indicator as the ingredient currently used to make a wetness indicator are not in line with our natural, eco-friendly diaper standards.

settings.title: Can your diapers lasts up to 12 hours?
settings.answer:
It is not our usual practice to claim 
 or to encourage parents to prolong wearing of disposable diaper. Although our baby diapers are able to last overnight, we always encourage parents to change your baby’s diaper regularly during the day to avoid rashes and bacterial or yeasts irritation, happen due to prolong exposure of baby’s urine direct on the skin.

settings.title: How absorbent are your diapers?
settings.answer:
Our chlorine-free baby diapers made with patented dual absorbent core technology from Japan, that are designed to lock-down urine and moist rapidly while keeping your baby’s skin dry and comfortable for longer period of time. 

Our baby diapers can last for long hours and definitely is fine for over night use.

settings.title: Do you have overnight diapers?
settings.answer: We do not have overnight diapers as our diapers are able to last overnight. Our patented dual core absorbency layers are made efficient for superior absorbency and at the same time, bulk-free, and suitable to be worn day and night.

settings.title: Are your diapers biodegradable?
settings.answer:
There is no disposable diaper is 100% biodegradable or compostable, especially the absorbent polymer, the adhesive tape, and the side leg cuff that are moist resistant, used on the diapers are not biodegradable.

Offspring Chlorine-Free baby diapers have been certified by the FSC (Forest Stewardship Council) C149807 for the materials used from sustainable forest. We try to be as eco-friendly as possible but at the same time, by providing practical functionality, and never compromise on busy parents convenience and lifestyle.

settings.title: Where are your diapers material come from?
settings.answer: We strive to provide you the best materials. Our materials are sourced globally from Japan, Europe, and US.

settings.title: What is the safety standard Offspring diapers have achieved?
settings.answer:
Our baby diapers are manufactured in an ISO 9001 clean room facility and are comply with the requirements under the U.S Consumer Product Safety Improvement Act of 2008 (16 CFR Part 1610).

The ink used on the diaper has passed the California Prop65 test and meet the requirements of the lead content of children’s products required by Section 101 of the CPSIA of 2008.

settings.title: What safety and environmental certifications you have?
settings.answer: We are proud that all of our products are certified by leading environmental intuitions parties. You may check out our certifications here

settings.title: Do you test on animals?
settings.answer: No. All of our products are certified Cruelty-Free.

Offspring products are designed with care by parents to parents. Crafted with an extensive knowledge of developing safe, effective and quality products through innovations, at the same time without compromising on sustainability and mother nature. We work closely with our experts all over the world, from material, to ingredients and to formulations, and our team of organic chemists and aromatherapist in Australia to develop our products with accordance to the strict guidelines of Ecocert Cosmos strict certification guidelines.

All of our products are adhered to eco-friendly, environmental standards and audited strictly. And we will continue to gain more certifications to build confidence of use of our products amongst the parents in the world.

settings.title: Does material of baby wipes really matters?
settings.answer: Yes! The material of baby wipes play an major role of a wipe. Offspring choses only biodegradable cellulose fibre from Austria, with USDA biobased preferred certification. It also able to hold and retain more liquid than the usual wipes, and that it won’t dry off easily as compare to normal plastic-based wipes. So it also means you can use less wipes for better effect!

settings.code:
Use Offspring Plant-Based Wipes Like This:

1. Don't waste the wipes! Fold them in half for multiple usages. Did you know that you usually only need ONE wipe for your baby's body?

2. Use one side of the wipe to cleanse mouth or any part of the skin, and the other side for other parts of the body.

3. Store at room temperature

4. Close lid firmly after each use to keep moist

5. Not flushable, but biodegradable in landfills!
